The De Beers Company controls the sale of 80 percent of the world's
gem diamonds. Its marketing cartel handles diamonds from the major
diamond-producing countries, setting production and price levels that
insure profitability. Cartel members chafe under the cartel's strict
policies, but De Beers keeps them in line.</SUM>
